# D-ops Project Overview

## Project Purpose
D-ops is a comprehensive business operations management system for tracking design, development, and operational tasks with automatic pricing calculations and client management capabilities.

## Core Business Logic
- **Task Management**: Record work hours across three categories (design, development, operation)
- **Client Management**: Maintain client information and associate tasks with specific clients
- **Pricing System**: Automatic price calculation based on category-specific hourly rates
- **Settlement Tracking**: Manage payment status from pending to completed
- **Analytics Dashboard**: Visual reports showing revenue, hours, and task distribution

## Key Entry Points
- Main application: [pages/_app.js](mdc:pages/_app.js)
- Dashboard: [pages/dashboard.js](mdc:pages/dashboard.js) 
- Task management: [pages/tasks/index.js](mdc:pages/tasks/index.js)
- Client management: [pages/clients/index.js](mdc:pages/clients/index.js)
- Authentication: [pages/login.js](mdc:pages/login.js)

## Database Schema
- **clients**: Client information and contact details
- **tasks**: Work records with hours, pricing, and settlement status
- **Authentication**: Handled by Supabase Auth with RLS policies

## Technology Context
- Frontend: Next.js 12.3.4 with React 17.0.2
- Styling: TailwindCSS with dark mode as default
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- Charts: Chart.js for data visualization
- Authentication: Supabase Auth with Row Level Security
